source_code.code:
public class Anon {
	void test() {
		class Type<S, T> {
			Type<String, String> t= new Type<String, String>(/*caret*/);
		}
	}
}

Bug.WithOutStack:
Using I20050920-0010, I got this exception.


STEPS TO REPRODUCE:
1) create a java project with a compilation unit containing:
package p;

public class Anon {
	void test() {
		class Type<S, T> {
			Type<String, String> t= new Type<String, String>(/*caret*/);
		}
	}
}
2) Put the cursor before the /*caret*/ comment.
3) Do code assist and select the second entry to create an anonymous entry. You
should get the stack trace.


